{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idf3c3e807-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc","identifier":"/us/usc/t35/s145"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"145"},"text":"§ 145.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Civil action to obtain patent","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"An applicant dissatisfied with the decision of the Patent Trial and Appeal Board in an appeal under section 134(a) may, unless appeal has been taken to the United States Court of Appeals for the Federal Circuit, have remedy by civil action against the Director in the United States District Court for the Eastern District of Virginia if commenced within such time after such decision, not less than sixty days, as the Director appoints. The court may adjudge that such applicant is entitled to receive a patent for his invention, as specified in any of his claims involved in the decision of the Patent Trial and Appeal Board, as the facts in the case may appear and such adjudication shall authorize the Director to issue such patent on compliance with the requirements of law. All the expenses of the proceedings shall be paid by the applicant.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idf3c3e808-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1952-07-19/ch950"},"text":"July 19, 1952, ch. 950","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/66/803"},"text":"66 Stat. 803","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/164/tI/s163/a/7"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–164, title I, § 163(a)(7)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1982-04-02"},"text":"Apr. 2, 1982","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/49"},"text":"96 Stat. 49","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/622/tII/s203/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–622, title II, § 203(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1984-11-08"},"text":"Nov. 8, 1984","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/98/3387"},"text":"98 Stat. 3387","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/113/dB/s1000/a/9/tIV/s4605/e"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–113, div. B, § 1000(a)(9) [title IV, §§ 4605(e), 4732(a)(10)(A)]","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1999-11-29"},"text":"Nov. 29, 1999","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/113/1536"},"text":"113 Stat. 1536","children":[],"tail":", 1501A–571, 1501A–582; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/273/dC/tIII/s13206/b/1/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–273, div. C, title III, § 13206(b)(1)(B)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-11-02"},"text":"Nov. 2, 2002","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/116/1906"},"text":"116 Stat. 1906","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/29"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–29","children":[],"tail":", §§ 3(j)(1), 9(a), 20(j), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2011-09-16"},"text":"Sept. 16, 2011","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/125/290"},"text":"125 Stat. 290","children":[],"tail":", 316, 335.)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idf3c3e809-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idf3c3e80a-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Based on Title 35, U.S.C., 1946 ed., § 63 (R.S. 4915, amended (1) ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1927-03-02/ch273/s11"},"text":"Mar. 2, 1927, ch. 273, § 11","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/44/1336"},"text":"44 Stat. 1336","children":[],"tail":", (2) "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1929-03-02/ch488/s2/b"},"text":"Mar. 2, 1929, ch. 488, § 2(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/45/1476"},"text":"45 Stat. 1476","children":[],"tail":", (3) "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1939-08-05/ch451/s4"},"text":"Aug. 5, 1939, ch. 451, § 4","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/53/1212"},"text":"53 Stat. 1212","children":[],"tail":")."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Bill in equity is changed to civil action and the section is restricted to exclude interferences which are covered by the next section. The time for filing the action is changed to the same as the time for appeal. The requirement for the applicant to file a copy of the decision in the Patent Office is omitted.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Language is changed.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idf3c3e80b-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idf3c3e80c-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2011—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/29/s20/j"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–29, § 20(j)","children":[],"tail":", struck out “of this title” after “134(a)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/29/s9/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–29, § 9(a)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “United States District Court for the Eastern District of Virginia” for “United States District Court for the District of Columbia”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/29/s3/j/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–29, § 3(j)(1)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “Patent Trial and Appeal Board” for “Board of Patent Appeals and Interferences” in two places."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2002—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/273"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–273","children":[],"tail":" made technical correction to directory language of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/113/s1000/a/9/tIV/s4732/a/10/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–113, § 1000(a)(9) [title IV, § 4732(a)(10)(A)]","children":[],"tail":". See 1999 Amendment note below."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1999—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/113/s1000/a/9/tIV/s4732/a/10/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–113, § 1000(a)(9) [title IV, § 4732(a)(10)(A)]","children":[],"tail":", as amended by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/273"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–273","children":[],"tail":", substituted “Director” for “Commissioner” wherever appearing."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/113/s1000/a/9/tIV/s4605/e"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–113, § 1000(a)(9) [title IV, § 4605(e)]","children":[],"tail":", inserted “(a)” after “section 134”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1984—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/622"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–622","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Patent Appeals and Interferences in an appeal under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t35/s134"},"text":"section 134 of this title","children":[],"tail":" may,” for “Appeals may” in first sentence and “Patent Appeals and Interferences” for “Appeals” in second sentence."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1982—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/164"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–164","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Court of Appeals for the Federal Circuit” for “Cour